 To find the intersection of the lines, we can solve the system of equations simultaneously. We have:
\[
\begin{align*}
9x - 4y &= 30 \quad \text{(1)} \\
7x + y &= 11 \quad \text{(2)}
\end{align*}
\]
We can eliminate $y$ by multiplying equation (2) by 4 and adding it to equation (1):
\[
\begin{align*}
7x + y &= 11 \\
28x + 4y &= 44
\end{align*}
\]
Adding these equations, we get:
\[
35x = 74 \implies x = \frac{74}{35}
\]
Substituting $x$ back into equation (2) to find $y$:
\[
\begin{align*}
7\left(\frac{74}{35}\right) + y &= 11 \\
\frac{49}{5} + y &= 11 \\
y &= 11 - \frac{49}{5} \\
y &= \frac{55 - 49}{5} \\
y &= \frac{6}{5}
\end{align*}
\]
</think> The answer is $\boxed{\left(\frac{74}{35}, \frac{6}{5}\right)}.$

